channel.description:
SPECS: CPU: Intel Celeron E3200 2.4GHZ Clocked @ 3.0GHZ Memory: 4GB GSKILL 1333MHZ RAM Motherboard: P5G43T-M PRO Harddrive: 500GB Western Digital Green Caviar CD DRIVE: Lite on CD Drive CPU Cooler: Really really really quiet Vortex 752: The stock intel cooler made a buzinning sound. If I set motherboard to manage cooler in quiet mode it wont get past 40C in prime 95 and its inaudible. If I have it set to max speed it wont get over 33C. I haven't tested since I put the top fan which sucks the hot air out, so it might be cooler. Plus the cooler blows on my northbridge and ram because it has fins which push air sideways. Video Card: GTS 250 1GB PSU: 600Watt OCZ PSU got this for 29.99. Case: Antec 300 (If Antec would just paint it like I did and add a window and cut those holes this case would sell like crazy I think.
BEFORE:
[img]http://i48.tinypic.com/1ileo9.jpg[/img]
LINK TO MORE BEFORE IMAGES: http://tinypic.com/a/1hhqb/2
AFTER:
[img]http://i48.tinypic.com/6xyxvm.jpg[/img]
What I did, custom holes for cable mangment with trim uchannel edging. Paint the thing black. Organized the cables, stripped the SATA connectors to make them right side up, and cut off the excess connectors.

item.title: New Build - Pictures
item.dc:creator: @mwiebelhaus mwiebelhaus
item.description:
@mwiebelhaus wrote:

Black Rostoleum Textured Spray Paint

http://www.rustoleum.com/product.asp?frm_product_id=20&SBL=1

2 Bottles is enough and all I did was one coat. Started drilling holes with my dad with air tools and dremel, then filed down the edges, then sprayed it started at 8:00 after seeing friendsat bojangles (fast food restruant), then drove home at 4:00 am in the morning and ate jack in the crack (jack in the box 24/7). Took forever but its worth it. If you guys decide to do it, do 2 coats. I chiped paint off easlily when doing the cable mangment, but the paint chippings you cant see because its on the back side (which is ok with me). Thats my 8800GT from my computer btw probably going to take it out when I leave since he wont be doing any gaming. Built in HD chipset is good enough plus I can use the HDMI and dont have to hook up an audio cable to his screen.
